{"kind":"blogger#post","id":"249021951281090347","blog":{"id":"2360593805083673688"},"published":"2011-04-29T08:36:00-07:00","updated":"2011-04-29T09:23:12-07:00","url":"http://www.quietlikehorses.com/2011/04/secrets-from-manicurist-for-perfect-diy.html","selfLink":"https://www.googleapis.com/blogger/v3/blogs/2360593805083673688/posts/249021951281090347","title":"Secrets from a Manicurist for Perfect DIY Nails","content":"<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><br /></div><a href=\"http://4.bp.blogspot.com/-RkDIiGOr8gY/TbpWqMyj0BI/AAAAAAAAGl4/QCqlM3Dsr3A/s1600/1.jpg\" onblur=\"try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}\"><img src=\"http://4.bp.blogspot.com/-RkDIiGOr8gY/TbpWqMyj0BI/AAAAAAAAGl4/QCqlM3Dsr3A/s1600/1.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" id=\"BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5600884369576415250\" style=\"display: block; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: auto; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: auto; text-align: center; cursor: pointer; width: 450px; height: 676px; \" /></a>In my book, if there is one telltale sign of a woman who has really got her act together, it would be a perfect manicure. Since I don't have the patience to maintain weekly manicures, I am always impressed by other women who do. My friend Stacy (the one with the <a href=\"http://bit.ly/gb5FK6\">great hair</a>) is one of these impossibly pulled-together women. Her nails are always trim and polished in a classy nude or other season-appropriate hue. Having spent over 3 years as a manicurist, she's definitely got the nail know-how I lack and happily shared how to get perfect salon nails without ever leaving home. <div><br /></div><div>Her nail kit musts: nail polish remover, cotton pads, alcohol, <a href=\"http://amzn.to/mkNm5C\">OPI Bond Aid</a>, base coat, OPI or Essie brand nail polish, <a href=\"http://amzn.to/k8lPQ0\">Nailtiques formula 2</a>, <a href=\"http://amzn.to/iGhhF6\">OPI Drip Dry</a>, nail file (180/400 grit), nail clippers, cuticle trimmers, and an <a href=\"http://amzn.to/kuYPfX\">orange stick</a> (not pictured).<br /><div><br /><div><a href=\"http://1.bp.blogspot.com/-Rk6EAtmv_ZQ/TbpWqLuEotI/AAAAAAAAGlw/R00Ocxwu7qA/s1600/2.jpg\" onblur=\"try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}\"><img src=\"http://1.bp.blogspot.com/-Rk6EAtmv_ZQ/TbpWqLuEotI/AAAAAAAAGlw/R00Ocxwu7qA/s1600/2.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" id=\"BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5600884369289159378\" style=\"display: block; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: auto; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: auto; text-align: center; cursor: pointer; width: 600px; height: 400px; \" /></a>First, start by removing any nail polish remnants from previous manicures.</div><div><br /><a href=\"http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-5KlGqdRzH0o/TbpWkmfA0XI/AAAAAAAAGlo/qfSfvZ1w-f4/s1600/3.jpg\" onblur=\"try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}\"><img src=\"http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-5KlGqdRzH0o/TbpWkmfA0XI/AAAAAAAAGlo/qfSfvZ1w-f4/s1600/3.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" id=\"BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5600884273394536818\" style=\"display: block; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: auto; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: auto; text-align: center; cursor: pointer; width: 600px; height: 400px; \" /></a>If your nails are on the longer side, trim them with nail clippers. Don't ever shorten them (if you have a long way to go) by filing them down as this can weaken them.</div><div><br /><a href=\"http://2.bp.blogspot.com/-wxNzPV0I78w/TbpWka14DjI/AAAAAAAAGlg/YkwT7Giw6kc/s1600/4.jpg\" onblur=\"try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}\"><img src=\"http://2.bp.blogspot.com/-wxNzPV0I78w/TbpWka14DjI/AAAAAAAAGlg/YkwT7Giw6kc/s1600/4.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" id=\"BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5600884270269206066\" style=\"display: block; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: auto; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: auto; text-align: center; cursor: pointer; width: 600px; height: 400px; \" /></a>Using the rougher side of the nail file, shape your nails. Then use the finer side of the nail file to smooth out any rough edges. </div><div><br /><a href=\"http://4.bp.blogspot.com/-VG_AM_2vuZU/TbpWkYK-X0I/AAAAAAAAGlY/ejv3FDYZgyY/s1600/5.jpg\" onblur=\"try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}\"><img src=\"http://4.bp.blogspot.com/-VG_AM_2vuZU/TbpWkYK-X0I/AAAAAAAAGlY/ejv3FDYZgyY/s1600/5.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" id=\"BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5600884269552394050\" style=\"display: block; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: auto; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: auto; text-align: center; cursor: pointer; width: 600px; height: 400px; \" /></a>Trim any hang nails you might have. Stacy doesn't believe in manicures which remove a lot of cuticle so her rule is only cut it if it's white and waving in the wind!</div><div><br /><a href=\"http://4.bp.blogspot.com/-CmgPsKTZwUA/TbpWkNnzS8I/AAAAAAAAGlQ/FDUDpBBetlM/s1600/6.jpg\" onblur=\"try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}\"><img src=\"http://4.bp.blogspot.com/-CmgPsKTZwUA/TbpWkNnzS8I/AAAAAAAAGlQ/FDUDpBBetlM/s1600/6.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" id=\"BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5600884266720512962\" style=\"display: block; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: auto; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: auto; text-align: center; cursor: pointer; width: 600px; height: 400px; \" /></a>Prep nails with a spritz of alcohol. This removes any oils and filing dust from the nails.</div><div><br /><a href=\"http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-ArXXOrFlpds/TbpWj2JnG2I/AAAAAAAAGlI/bGoP2Zcttko/s1600/7.jpg\" onblur=\"try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}\"><img src=\"http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-ArXXOrFlpds/TbpWj2JnG2I/AAAAAAAAGlI/bGoP2Zcttko/s1600/7.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" id=\"BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5600884260419869538\" style=\"display: block; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: auto; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: auto; text-align: center; cursor: pointer; width: 600px; height: 400px; \" /></a>Apply a coat of Bond Aid, a nail dehydrator which will ensure your polish sticks.</div><div><br /><a href=\"http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-WO4aJIuP5CM/TbpWaEveuGI/AAAAAAAAGlA/TkxrE5nJtDs/s1600/8.jpg\" onblur=\"try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}\"><img src=\"http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-WO4aJIuP5CM/TbpWaEveuGI/AAAAAAAAGlA/TkxrE5nJtDs/s1600/8.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" id=\"BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5600884092538108002\" style=\"display: block; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: auto; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: auto; text-align: center; cursor: pointer; width: 600px; height: 400px; \" /></a>Next, apply a base coat.</div><div><br /><a href=\"http://1.bp.blogspot.com/-nne6ZT3bZOI/TbpWZ5Q9k6I/AAAAAAAAGk4/ruLIZI1YtQA/s1600/9.jpg\" onblur=\"try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}\"><img src=\"http://1.bp.blogspot.com/-nne6ZT3bZOI/TbpWZ5Q9k6I/AAAAAAAAGk4/ruLIZI1YtQA/s1600/9.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" id=\"BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5600884089457316770\" style=\"display: block; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: auto; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: auto; text-align: center; cursor: pointer; width: 600px; height: 400px; \" /></a>Apply 2 coats of your nail color. Stacy's wearing OPI in <a href=\"http://amzn.to/jkFwB2\">Most Honorable</a>. </div><div><br /><a href=\"http://2.bp.blogspot.com/-sFZ3tN2EnRc/TbpWZlBzokI/AAAAAAAAGkw/pbS-e_57-J8/s1600/10.jpg\" onblur=\"try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}\"><img src=\"http://2.bp.blogspot.com/-sFZ3tN2EnRc/TbpWZlBzokI/AAAAAAAAGkw/pbS-e_57-J8/s1600/10.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" id=\"BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5600884084025041474\" style=\"display: block; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: auto; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: auto; text-align: center; cursor: pointer; width: 600px; height: 400px; \" /></a>Use an orange stick to clean up any excess polish that gets on your cuticles or skin. (Having just discovered orange sticks, I wish I had learned about them earlier -- they are so simple, yet so helpful!)</div><div><br /><a href=\"http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-NLv83Ag5yOA/TbpWZcFJTWI/AAAAAAAAGko/lLDXjGTKgiY/s1600/11.jpg\" onblur=\"try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}\"><img src=\"http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-NLv83Ag5yOA/TbpWZcFJTWI/AAAAAAAAGko/lLDXjGTKgiY/s1600/11.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" id=\"BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5600884081623125346\" style=\"display: block; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: auto; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: auto; text-align: center; cursor: pointer; width: 600px; height: 400px; \" /></a>Stacy swears by Nailtiques Formula 2 as a top coat. (I've used it when my nails were splitting and it really helped.) </div><div><br /><a href=\"http://2.bp.blogspot.com/-nTA9Juqh70M/TbpWZJEpBiI/AAAAAAAAGkg/rUYREnzqOKY/s1600/12.jpg\" onblur=\"try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}\"><img src=\"http://2.bp.blogspot.com/-nTA9Juqh70M/TbpWZJEpBiI/AAAAAAAAGkg/rUYREnzqOKY/s1600/12.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" id=\"BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5600884076520736290\" style=\"display: block; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: auto; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: auto; text-align: center; cursor: pointer; width: 600px; height: 400px; \" /></a>Finally, squeeze a few OPI Drip Dry drops over your manicure. This helps set your polish so they can dry quicker and they lend a little extra shine. Your nails will be dry to the touch in 10 minutes and fully dry in 2 hours. Manicures given a little extra care and attention (see Stacy's additional tips below) last between 7 and 10 days. </div></div></div><div><br /></div><div><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 238); -webkit-text-decorations-in-effect: underline; \"></span></div><div style=\"text-align: center;\"><br /><a href=\"http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-d8Adl_8I9ZI/Tbrkv40rwnI/AAAAAAAAGmA/fSFkbwgmZas/s1600/nail%2Btips%2B%25281%2529.jpg\" onblur=\"try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}\"><img style=\"display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 600px; height: 400px;\" src=\"http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-d8Adl_8I9ZI/Tbrkv40rwnI/AAAAAAAAGmA/fSFkbwgmZas/s1600/nail%2Btips%2B%25281%2529.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" id=\"BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5601040597946974834\" /></a><br /></div><div style=\"text-align: left;\">(A big thanks to Stacy and <a href=\"http://on.fb.me/kkVlg1\">Daniel Garcia</a> for the photography help!)</div>","author":{"id":"06629562195146939698","displayName":"Sobrina Tung","url":"http://www.blogger.com/profile/06629562195146939698","image":{"url":"http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_mkw1MyhyGTY/TI8X4CO5nWI/AAAAAAAAERk/4p5D74gYdFE/S45/me.JPG"}},"replies":{"totalItems":"2","selfLink":"https://www.googleapis.com/blogger/v3/blogs/2360593805083673688/posts/249021951281090347/comments"},"labels":["To Wear"]}